All Classes and Interfaces

Class
Description
Block
Represents a block (subgrid) in a Sudoku board.
Board
Represents the complete Sudoku board.
BoardAdapter
An abstract implementation of the IBoard interface.
Cell
Represents a single cell in a Sudoku grid.
CellErrorAnimator
This class is responsible for animating the error effect on a TextField.
CellHelpAnimator
This class is responsible for animating a visual hint on a TextField.
CellValueConverter
Converts between Integer values and their String representations for use in JavaFX controls like TextField.
Hint
Represents a hint for the Sudoku board.
IBoard
Interface representing a Sudoku board.
Main
Main class that serves as the entry point of the JavaFX Sudoku application.
StartController
Controller for the start screen of the Sudoku game.
SudokuController
Controller class for the main Sudoku game view.
SudokuStage
Represents the main window (stage) of the Sudoku application.
TextFilter
Utility class that provides a TextFormatter to restrict user input in a TextField to only digits from 1 to 6.
VictoryController
Controller class for the victory screen, which is displayed when the player wins the game.
